components.content: The bees need the cotton plants for food. The cotton plants are the resources the bees need to survive. 1 square of cotton has enough resources for 1 bee hive.
What is the total number of hives that the cotton plants can support?
There are 10 squares of cotton plants, which is enough resources for 10 beehives. Lucy already has 5 beehives, so she can add 5 more.
